<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>
<ns0:Document xmlns:ns0="http://www.suscopts.org/CopticReader" Pascha="true" FixedDateDocument="true">
   <ns0:ForceSeason id="Fasts ^ PaschaWeek ^ WatosDays ^ Weekend ^ JoyousSaturday ^ Saturdays ^ FuneralTune ^ SeasonOfAirAndFruits">
      <ns0:Title>
         <ns0:Language id="English">Midnight Praises</ns0:Language>      
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">تسبحة نصف الليل</ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Title>
      
      <ns0:Role id="Priest">
         <ns0:Comment>
            <ns0:Language id="English">
               The priest and deacons put on their service vestments, and the veil of the sanctuary is opened.  
            </ns0:Language>
         </ns0:Comment>
         
         <ns0:Comment>
            <ns0:Language id="English">
               The priest stands before the sanctuary facing the east with his head uncovered, and holds the book of Psalms, wrapped in a white linen veil and chants “Glory be to our God (<ns0:span class="Coptic">Doxaci o~ ye~oc /~mwn Al</ns0:span>)” in its apocalyptic tune, followed by Psalm 151:
            </ns0:Language>
         </ns0:Comment>
      </ns0:Role>
      
      <ns0:Role id="People">
         <ns0:Section expanded="true" antiphonePitch="1">
      <ns0:Title>
         <ns0:Language id="English">Psalm 151</ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">مزمور 151</ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Title>
      
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Doxaci o~Yeoc /~mwn. All/louia: Piw~ou va Pennou] pe.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            Glory be to our God. Alleluia: Glory be to our God.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            المجد لله. الليلويا. المجد هو لإلهنا.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
      
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Anok pe pikouji n~q~r/i qen nac~n/ou: ouoh n~a~lou qen p~/i n~te paiwt: naia~moni n~nie~cwou n~te paiwt.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            I am small among my brothers: and a boy in my father’s house: I tended my father’s sheep.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            أنا الصغير في اخوتي والحدث في بيت أبي ، كنت راعياً غنم أبي.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
      
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Najij auyamio~ n~ouorganon: ouoh nat/b auhwtp n~ou'alt/rion: A#l# (3).
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            My hands made an organ: and my fingers tuned a psaltery: Alleluia (3).
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            يداى صنعتا الأرغن، وأصابعي ألفت المزمار،  الليلويا (3).
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
      
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Ouoh nim pe y~nas~tame Pa[oic: n~yof pe P[#c#: n~yof safcwtem e~ouon niben etws e~h~r/i oub/f.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            And who shall tell my Lord? He is The Lord: He listens+ to everyone that cries up to Him.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            من هو الذي يخبر سيدي ، هو الرب الذي يستجيب لجميع الذين يصرخون إليه.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
      
      <ns0:Comment>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            + Habitual tense meaning always listens; is used to listening.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Comment>
      
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Nyof afouwrp m~pefaggeloc: ouoh afolt e~bolqen nie~cwou n~te paiwt: ouoh afyahct qen v~neh n~te pefywhc: A#l# (3).
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            He sent His angel, and took me from my father’s sheep: and anointed me with His anointing oil: Alleluia (3).
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            وهو أرسل ملاكه ورفعني من غنم أبي ، ومسحني بدهن مسحته،  الليلويا (3).
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
      
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Nac~n/ou naneu ouoh hannis] ne: ouoh m~pef]ma] n~q/tou n~je P[#c#.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            My brothers are handsome and great, but the Lord did not take pleasure in them.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            أخوتي حسان وهم اكبر منى ، والرب لم يسر بهم.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
      
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Aii~ e~bol e~h~ren piAllovuloc: afcahoui e~roi qen nefi~dwlon: A#l# (3).
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            I went out to meet the Philistine: and he cursed me with his idols: Alleluia (3).
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            خرجت للقاء الفلسطيني فلعني بأوثانه الليلويا (3).
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
      
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Anok de aiywkem n~tefc/fi et,/ n~totf aiw~li n~tef a~ve.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            But I drew his sword which he had+, and beheaded him++.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            فاستليت سيفه الذي كان بيده ونزعت رأسه عنه.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
      
      <ns0:Comment>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            <ns0:ul>
               <ns0:li>+ Lit. “which is in his hand”</ns0:li>
               <ns0:li>++ Lit. “lifted his head”</ns0:li>               
            </ns0:ul>
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Comment>
      
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Ouoh aiw~li n~ou[isipi e~bolqen nens/ri m~Pic~ra/l.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            And removed+ reproach from the children of Israel.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            ونزعت العار عن بني اسرائيل.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
      
      <ns0:Comment>
         <ns0:Language id="English">               
            + Lit. “lifted”
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Comment>
      
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            All/louia: all/louia: all/louia. Piw~ou va Pennou] pe.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            Alleluia, Alleluia, Alleluia. Glory be to our God.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            الليلويا الليلويا الليلويا. المجد هو لإلهنا.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>

   </ns0:Section>
</ns0:Role>
      
      <ns0:Role id="Priest">
         <ns0:Comment>
            <ns0:Language id="English">
               The priest carries the book of Psalms and proceeds around the church three times with the deacons while chanting the "Let us give thanks (<ns0:span class="Coptic">Marenouwnh e~bol</ns0:span>)."
            </ns0:Language>
         </ns0:Comment>
         
         <ns0:Comment>
            <ns0:Language id="English">
               Please note that all the Praises are chanted by alternating one verse from inside the sanctuary and one verse from outside the sanctuary.   
            </ns0:Language>
         </ns0:Comment>
      </ns0:Role>
      
      <ns0:Role id="People">
         <ns0:Section expanded="true" antiphonePitch="1" antiphoneStart="true">
      <ns0:Title>         
         <ns0:Language id="English">Adam Psali (Lobsh) for the Second Canticle</ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">مديح آدام</ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">Marenouwnh...</ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Title>
   
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Marenouwnh e~bol:  m~Pi,~rictoc Pennou]: nem piiero'alt/c: Dauid pip~rov/t/c.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            Let us give thanks: unto Christ our God: with David the Prophet: and the holy Psalmist.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            فلنشكرْ المسيح إلهَنا، مع المُرتِّل داود النبي.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
   
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Je afyamio~ n~niv/oui: nem noudunamic: afhicen] m~pikahi: e~h~r/i hijen nimwou.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            For He has made the heavens: and all its hosts: and established the earth: on the waters.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            لأنه خلقَ السماوات وجنودَها، وأسسَ الأرضَ على المياه.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
   
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Nai nis] m~vwct/r: pir/ nem piioh: af,au eue~rouwini: qen pic~terew~ma.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            These two great lights: the sun and the moon: He has made to enlighten: the firmament.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            هذان الكوكبان العظيمان الشمسُ والقمر، جعلَهما يُنيرانِ في الفَلَك.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
   
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Afi~ni n~hany/ou: e~bol qen  nefa~hwr: afnifi n~ca nis~s/n: san~touviri e~bol.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            He brought forth the winds: out of His treasures: He breathed unto the trees: and they blossomed.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            أخرجَ الرياح مِن خباياه، نفخَ في الأشجار حتى أزهرَت.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
   
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Afhwou n~oumounhwou: hijen p~ho m~p~kahi: san~tefrwt e~p~swi: n~tef] m~pefoutah.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            He caused the rain to fall: upon the face of the earth: and it sprouted: and gave its fruit.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            أمطرَ مطراً على وجهِ الأرض، حتى أنبتَت وأعطَت ثمرَها.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
   
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Afi~ni n~oumwou: e~bolqen  oupetra: aft~co m~peflaoc: n~h~r/i hi p~safe.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            He brought forth water: out of a rock: and gave it to His people: in the wilderness.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            أخرجَ ماءً مِن صخرةٍ صماء، وسقى شعبَهُ في البرِّية.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
   
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Afyamio m~pirwmi: kata pefi~ni: nem tefhikwn: eyrefc~mou e~rof.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            He made man: in His image: and His likeness: that He may bless him.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            صنعَ الإنسان كشبهِهِ، وصورتِهِ لكي يباركَهُ.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
   
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Marenhwc e~rof: ten[ici m~pefran: tenouwnh naf e~bol: je pefnai sop sa e~neh.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            Let us praise Him: and exalt His name: and give thanks to Him: His mercy endures forever.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            فلنسبحْهُ ونرفعْ اسمَهُ، ونشكرْهُ لأن رحمتَهُ كائنةٌ إلى الأبد.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
   
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Hiten nieu,/: n~te piiero'alt/c Dauid: Po#c# a~rih~mot nan: m~pi,w e~bol n~te nennobi.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            Through the prayers: of David the holy Psalmist: O Lord, grant us: the forgiveness of our sins.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            بصلواتِ المُرتِّل داود، يا ربّ أنعِم لنا بمغفِرَة خطايانا.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
   
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Hiten nip~recbia: n~te ]yeo~tokoc e#y#u# Maria: Po#c# a~rih~mot nan: m~pi,w e~bol n~te nennobi.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            Through the intercessions: of the Mother of God Saint Mary: O Lord, grant us: the forgiveness of our sins.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            بشفاعات والدةِ الإلهِ القديسة مريم، يا ربّ أنعِم لنا بمغفِرَة خطايانا.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
   
      <ns0:Text>
         <ns0:Language id="Coptic">
            Hiten nip~recbia: n~te p~,oroc t/rf n~te niaggeloc: Po#c# a~rih~mot nan: m~pi,w e~bol n~te nennobi.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="English">
            Through the intercessions: of the whole chorus of angels: O Lord, grant us: the forgiveness of our sins.
         </ns0:Language>
         <ns0:Language id="Arabic">
            بشفاعات كلِّ صفوفِ الملائكة، يا ربّ أنعِم لنا بمغفِرَة خطايانا.
         </ns0:Language>
      </ns0:Text>
      
      <ns0:Group>
      <ns0:Season id="NativityPeriod | NativityParamoun | Circumcision">
         <ns0:Comment>
            <ns0:Language id="English">         
               From the Paramoun of the Nativity to the Feast of the Circumcision:
            </ns0:Language>
         </ns0:Comment>
      </ns0:Season>
      
      <ns0:Season id="TheophanyPeriod | TheophanyParamoun">
